            "id": "60a19d6583ba433ab1fe1",
            "questionText": "Consider an oil slick floating on water. The refractive index of the oil is $!$n_{oil} = 1.45$!$, and the refractive index of the water is $!$n_{water} = 1.33$!$. Suppose a region of the slick appears green in color, corresponding to a wavelength of $!$\\lambda = 520 \\text{ nm}$!$ in air. Assuming that the green color results from constructive interference, calculate the minimum thickness $!$t$!$ of the oil slick in that region. Assume near-normal incidence of light.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "2830a03ae4924bf9b8531",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the interference condition for a thin film when one of the reflected beams undergoes a $\\pi$ phase shift. Please select the correct formula representing the condition for constructive interference in this scenario.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "0385489a-6c6b-46fb-974a-29b815bc23e2"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$2n_{oil}t = (m + \\frac{1}{2})\\lambda$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$2n_{oil}t = m\\lambda$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$n_{oil}t = (m + \\frac{1}{2})\\lambda$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "32b2d2e1eabc4207baf44",
                    "stepText": "Great, now that you have the interference condition, consider the fact that we are looking for the minimum thickness. This corresponds to choosing the smallest non-negative integer value for m. Which option shows the correct condition when m is set to this minimal value?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "0385489a-6c6b-46fb-974a-29b815bc23e2"
                    ],
                    "options": [
