        {
            "id": "7f31dbbc22624e5da59e5",
            "questionText": "In a double-slit experiment, light with a wavelength of $!$\\lambda = 632.8 \\text{ nm}$!$ is incident on two slits separated by a distance of $!$d = 0.2 \\text{ mm}$!$. The interference pattern is observed on a screen placed at a distance of $!$D = 3.0 \\text{ m}$!$ from the slits. Determine the distance $!$s$!$ on the screen between the central bright fringe and the third bright fringe ($!$n = 3$!$).",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "7815ab5de9524067afff4",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by recalling which formula we should use to determine the position of the bright fringes in a double-slit experiment. Please select the correct formula from the options below.",
